ainer (<b>3</b>) to be closed, wherein said lateral surface faces the longitudinal axis (<b>5</b>). The sealing elements (<b>12, 16</b>) arranged on the shaft part (<b>6</b>) are arranged in succession in a circumferential plane and in the circumferential direction of the shaft part (<b>6</b>). At least one supporting element (<b>31, 33</b>) is arranged and extends between the sealing element (<b>12, 16</b>) and the outer surface (<b>9</b>) of the shaft part (<b>6</b>).</p></abstract></us-patent-application>